    <h1 class="title">Vision in Humans and Nocturnal Animals</h1>
    
    <p><strong>Group 3, Bapp GEOICT, 4.1</strong></p>
    <p>Remote sensing is a sensation that allows us to gather 
information about the environment through various means. This document 
explores the fascinating comparison between human vision and that of 
nocturnal animals, highlighting the advancements in technology inspired 
by these unique adaptations.</p>
    
    <p><strong>Pitching Vision:</strong> The concept of vision, both 
biological and technological, is crucial in understanding our world. 
This document aims to elucidate how the remarkable visual adaptations of
 nocturnal animals can inform and enhance our technological capabilities
 in low-light environments.</p>

